The paper discusses justification logics, which are a type of modal logic, and their potential application in modeling the behavior and interaction of agents in distributed systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Multiagent Systems (cs.MA), Programming Languages (cs.PL), and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). Of these, cs.LO is the most likely category, as the paper focuses on a specific type of logic and its properties. However, the paper's discussion of distributed systems and agents also makes cs.AI, cs.MA, and cs.DC likely categories. Finally, the paper's potential application in programming languages suggests that cs.PL could also be a relevant category.
